CMS tops marketer list in customer satisfaction

02/06/2001
Gas Daily
(c) Copyright 2001 Pasha Publications, Inc. All Rights Reserved.


The latest customer satisfaction report by Mastio & Co. finds CMS Energy on
top among 68 of the nation's marketers in areas such as reliability, price
and ease of business.


Mastio surveyed 1,200 industrials, local distribution companies, electric
generators, independent power producers, marketers and producers for the
report, ranking the marketers on 39 customer satisfaction attributes.


The top 20, in order, are: CMS, Reliant, Williams, TXU Energy Trading , Enron
North America, Southern Co. Energy Marketing , Conoco, Oneok, TransCanada, El
Paso Energy Marketing , Aquila Energy, PanCanadian Energy Services, BP, Duke
Energy Trading , Dynegy Marketing & Trade, Exxon Mobil Gas Marketing , Coral
Energy Resources, Sempra Energy Trading and Koch Energy Trading .


Of those, Reliant Energy had the highest two-year average, while Koch Energy
Trading had the lowest two-year average. Enron North America and Texaco Gas
Marketing showed the greatest improvement, while Sempra and Koch showed the
most significant decline. A total of 43 marketers improved their scores,
while 27 declined. This is the fourth such index for marketers from St.
Joseph, Mo.-based Mastio.


"Many marketers focus on the niche customers while ignoring their core
customers," noted Bart Thedinger, vice president/senior partner of Mastio &
Co.


